            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "OpenAI",
                    "bold": true
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Use async clients to manage concurrency, cache embeddings to reduce API calls, and set fallback mechanisms for downtime.\nEnsure both implementations include logging and metrics collection for production monitoring."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use Cases and Recommendations for API Teams"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Choose BGE M3 for high-volume, low-latency applications such as real-time recommendation systems or multilingual search where data privacy is paramount. Opt for OpenAI embeddings when rapid prototyping or leveraging pre-trained models without infrastructure overhead is preferred. For hybrid approaches, consider using BGE M3 for core services and OpenAI for auxiliary tasks. Always conduct A/B testing to align with your specific performance and cost requirements."
